4. Backend Modules
   4.1 Auth Module

Features:

User registration

Login

JWT authentication

Refresh tokens

Password hashing (bcrypt)

Optional future:

Two-factor authentication

4.2 User Module

Stores:

Profile data

Risk preference

Simulation history

Saved plans

4.3 Investment Module

Handles:

Investment categories

Expected return ranges

Risk level

Liquidity

Lock-in period

Metadata

Admin controlled.

4.4 Risk Engine Module

Deterministic scoring system:

Inputs:

Time horizon

Liquidity need

Risk tolerance

Outputs:

Conservative

Balanced

Aggressive

Rule-based only. No AI here.

4.5 Allocation Engine Module

Logic:

Predefined allocation matrix per risk profile

Adjusted by time horizon

Returns percentage breakdown

Example:

Conservative:

50% FD

25% Mutual Fund

15% Bonds

10% Gold

Aggressive:

60% Stocks

20% Mutual Funds

10% Business

10% Gold

4.6 Projection Engine Module

Implements compound growth:

Inputs:

Initial capital

Monthly contribution

Annual return rate

Time horizon

Produces:

Conservative projection

Expected projection

Optimistic projection

Uses formula:

Future Value = P(1+r)^t + Monthly Contribution Growth

4.7 AI Explanation Module

Function:

Accept allocation + projection output

Generate structured explanation

Provide educational narrative

Restrictions:

No guaranteed language

No price prediction

No stock-specific advice

Integration:

OpenAI API via backend only

Prompt templates stored in backend

